POLICE_AND_THIEVES(n, k, arr)
1. Sort the array arr in non-decreasing order.
2. Initialize two pointers i and j to the first and second elements of the array.
3. While i < n and j < n:
     a. If arr[j] - arr[i] <= k, increment j.
     b. If arr[j] - arr[i] > k, increment i.
     c. If i == j, increment j.
4. Return the number of thieves caught (j - i).
